23
00:01:03,220 --> 00:01:04,940
Don't put too much on a card.

24
00:01:04,940 --> 00:01:08,380
OK, so if I've got note cards, they're not very big.

25
00:01:08,380 --> 00:01:09,580
OK, that's a whole purpose, right?

26
00:01:09,580 --> 00:01:12,730
Is they don't get in the way, they're not too much of a visual distraction

27
00:01:12,730 --> 00:01:13,940
between me and my audience.

28
00:01:13,940 --> 00:01:15,090
So they're not that big.

29
00:01:15,090 --> 00:01:18,070
Don't put too much on a card.

30
00:01:18,070 --> 00:01:23,060
Better to have more cards then having text that you have to read like this.

31
00:01:23,060 --> 00:01:26,440
A good note card should be able to be read from arm's length, right?

32
00:01:26,440 --> 00:01:31,810
You're just referencing and not waving it around when you're not using it.

33
00:01:31,810 --> 00:01:33,330
So don't put too much on a note card.

34
00:01:33,330 --> 00:01:35,260
As part of that, you really probably don't need to

35
00:01:35,260 --> 00:01:37,170
write out full sentences.

36
00:01:37,170 --> 00:01:40,545
If it's a reminder of where you want to go, they're just notes to help aid

37
