51
00:02:15,710 --> 00:02:19,310
If you've got main points and sub-points, put a single

52
00:02:19,310 --> 00:02:20,540
sub-point on a card.

53
00:02:20,540 --> 00:02:23,370
Because then you've got a nice transition point, right?

54
00:02:23,370 --> 00:02:25,710
So let's say you're in your 1A.

55
00:02:25,710 --> 00:02:27,090
You've got that on a card.

56
00:02:27,090 --> 00:02:33,230
Then as your transitioning to your 1B, you've got a visual marker of that

57
00:02:33,230 --> 00:02:35,770
break as well as an auditory one.

58
00:02:35,770 --> 00:02:39,070
It's a nice way of keeping things easy to follow.

59
00:02:39,070 --> 00:02:41,460
If they're short points, put a full point on there.

60
00:02:41,460 --> 00:02:44,610
But really, what you're trying to do is think about when you're going to

61
00:02:44,610 --> 00:02:46,730
take a break in the presentation.

62
00:02:46,730 --> 00:02:50,920
That's maybe when you're going to want to have a card shift.

63
00:02:50,920 --> 00:02:52,320
Shorten words and phrases.

64
00:02:52,320 --> 00:02:55,810
No one should be seeing your cards but you, and so just put enough on there

65
00:02:55,810 --> 00:02:57,930
to remind you of what you wanted to say.

66
00:02:57,930 --> 00:03:01,160
And I think it is a good point, a strategic point, to

67
00:03:01,160 --> 00:03:02,910
number your cards, right?

68
00:03:02,910 --> 00:03:05,420
So one, two, three, four, so on and so forth.

69
00:03:05,420 --> 00:03:06,220
Why?

70
00:03:06,220 --> 00:03:11,760
Let's say you're delivering a speech in a hurricane, because that's a neat

71
00:03:11,760 --> 00:03:13,440
place to deliver a speech.

72
00:03:13,440 --> 00:03:15,690
And you're speaking and you're talking.

73
00:03:15,690 --> 00:03:19,960
And as you go to transition that point, psh!

74
00:03:19,960 --> 00:03:21,090
It's gone.

75
00:03:21,090 --> 00:03:26,010
And so then, you're in the position of having to it just reach down and

76
00:03:26,010 --> 00:03:26,910
collect them.

77
00:03:26,910 --> 00:03:32,150
And then you've got your note cards, and oh, I, where was I?

78
00:03:32,150 --> 00:03:33,440
Ha ha, this was--

79
00:03:33,440 --> 00:03:35,990
no, that's-- that's not even my note card.

80
00:03:35,990 --> 00:03:37,920
So number your cards, OK?

81
00:03:37,920 --> 00:03:41,200
It could save you some time, some heartache, some stress later on if

82
00:03:41,200 --> 00:03:42,040
something happens.

83
00:03:42,040 --> 00:03:44,230
Helps keep you on track.

84
