00:05:35,460 --> 00:05:38,110
So sometimes, you're going to want written notes.

120
00:05:38,110 --> 00:05:40,670
Let's say you want to work with your outline.

121
00:05:40,670 --> 00:05:41,650
I think that's great.

122
00:05:41,650 --> 00:05:44,970
That's how I often speak, is with an outline.

123
00:05:44,970 --> 00:05:48,290
But what you want to do is make sure that outline is something that will

124
00:05:48,290 --> 00:05:52,450
actually aid you in that speech performance.

125
00:05:52,450 --> 00:05:54,440
So you're walking a delicate line here.

126
00:05:54,440 --> 00:05:57,150
Too much text and you won't be able to quickly find your

127
00:05:57,150 --> 00:05:58,530
place on that outline.

128
00:05:58,530 --> 00:06:01,060
Too little text, and the notes aren't all that helpful.

129
00:06:01,060 --> 00:06:06,800
